    <!-- Detailed Performance Section -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">In-Depth Performance</h2>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Image Quality & Sensor Performance</h3>
        <p>
          The 24-megapixel partially stacked sensor is a sweet spot for hybrid
          shooting. While not as high-resolution as the Z8 or Z9, it delivers
          exceptional image quality with larger pixels that excel in low light.
          The sensor's partial stacking enables improved readout speeds, reducing
          rolling shutter and enabling faster burst rates.
        </p>
        <p>
          Dynamic range is outstanding, capturing approximately 14 stops at base
          ISO. High-ISO performance is particularly impressiveâ€”ISO 6400 delivers
          clean, usable images, and even ISO 12800 maintains excellent detail
          with minimal noise reduction needed. This makes the Z6 III ideal for
          wedding photographers, event coverage, and available-light work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Autofocus Revolution</h3>
        <p>
          Nikon has made massive strides in autofocus with the Z6 III. The
          493-point hybrid AF system now includes deep learning-based subject
          detection for 9 subject types: people, dogs, cats, birds, cars,
          motorcycles, bicycles, trains, and airplanes. Eye detection works
          reliably even when subjects are small in frame or partially obscured.
        </p>
        <p>
          3D-Tracking has been refined to stick to subjects with remarkable
          tenacity. In real-world testing, the camera maintained focus on erratic
          subjects (playing children, flying birds) with a success rate comparable
          to Sony's excellent system. Low-light AF performance is exceptional,
          working down to -9 EVâ€”usable in near-dark conditions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Video Capabilities</h3>
        <p>
          The Z6 III's video features are where Nikon flexes its hybrid muscles.
          Internal 6K 60p N-RAW recording (to CFexpress Type B cards) provides
          professional latitude for color grading. For most users, the 5.4K 60p
          oversampled 4K is exceptionalâ€”delivering sharp, detailed footage with
          excellent color science.
        </p>
        <p>
          4K 120p enables high-quality slow motion without sensor crop, a
          significant advantage over many competitors. The addition of internal
          ProRes 422 HQ gives editors maximum flexibility. Heat management is
          excellentâ€”continuous 4K recording is possible for over 2 hours, and
          even 6K N-RAW can record for extended periods without overheating.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="content-block">
        <h3>Ergonomics & Build</h3>
        <p>
          Nikon's ergonomics remain industry-leading. The Z6 III features a deep,
          sculpted grip that's comfortable even with large telephoto lenses. Button
          layout is logical, with dedicated ISO, drive mode, and video record
          buttons. The four-axis tilting touchscreen is a practical compromiseâ€”more
          versatile than fixed, yet more robust than fully articulating.
        </p>
        <p>
          Build quality is exceptional, with magnesium alloy construction and
          comprehensive weather sealing. The EN-EL15c battery provides excellent
          longevityâ€”approximately 410 shots per charge (CIPA), with real-world
          performance often exceeding 600-800 shots. USB-C charging and power
          delivery enable all-day shooting when needed.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Ideal Lenses -->
